  "doc_id": "14418",
  "text": "There is a variation in treatment patterns within and outside the United States [CITATION_1] . One commonly used regimen includes treatment with 40 mg of prednisone for four weeks, followed by a taper by 5 mg each week for a total of an 11-week course [CITATION_2] . Response usually occurs within two to four months. Moon et al. have suggested that two weeks may be sufficient to determine response, which may be of particular importance in differentiating AIP from pancreatic cancer without delay [CITATION_3] .",
